        "timestamp": 1658435442
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think even if we decide we want to design a new bot icon, it seems like the first step at a codebase level would be to switch the settings UI to use the same icon resource, so they're consistent.</p>",
        "id": 1408294,
        "sender_full_name": "Tim Abbott",
        "timestamp": 1658435499
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Using the same icon in the settings as in bot messages and the bot profile makes sense to me!</p>",
        "id": 1408430,
        "sender_full_name": "Alya Abbott",
        "timestamp": 1658441052
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The particular one we've got has always felt a bit sinister to me somehow. <a href=\"/user_uploads/2/44/Vu4HGPjkAf9RxyQnPXqjf6rZ/Screen-Shot-2022-07-21-at-3.03.30-PM.png\">Screen-Shot-2022-07-21-at-3.03.30-PM.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/44/Vu4HGPjkAf9RxyQnPXqjf6rZ/Screen-Shot-2022-07-21-at-3.03.30-PM.png\" title=\"Screen-Shot-2022-07-21-at-3.03.30-PM.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/2/44/Vu4HGPjkAf9RxyQnPXqjf6rZ/Screen-Shot-2022-07-21-at-3.03.30-PM.png\"></a></div>",
        "id": 1408431,
        "sender_full_name": "Alya Abbott",
        "timestamp": 1658441085
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Do folks have feedback on <span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"24433\">Raymond Asogwa</span> 's proposal above? I wonder if we can make it look a bit friendlier.</p>",
        "id": 1408432,
        "sender_full_name": "Alya Abbott",
        "timestamp": 1658441136
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For reference, icon updates for the gear settings menu are discussed in <a class=\"stream-topic\" data-stream-id=\"101\" href=\"/#narrow/stream/101-design/topic/UI.20redesign.3A.20gear.20menu\">#design &gt; UI redesign: gear menu</a> .</p>",
        "id": 1408433,
        "sender_full_name": "Alya Abbott",
        "timestamp": 1658441450
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ok, lets hold on change of all icons, which <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"24433\">@Raymond Asogwa</span> suggested <a href=\"/user_uploads/2/0/V6N4qlmGJctqQks9igj-35iS/image.png\">image.png</a> </p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/0/V6N4qlmGJctqQks9igj-35iS/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/2/0/V6N4qlmGJctqQks9igj-35iS/image.png\"></a></div><p>Let's look how the new icon looks next to Notification bot name.</p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"24433\">@Raymond Asogwa</span> would you be able to show current/legacy design with just 1 icon change and show those places in a fullscreen way, so we would see icon in settings and icon in a message stream?</p>",
        "id": 1409687,
        "sender_full_name": "Vlad Korobov",
        "timestamp": 1658690569
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/89/9ymUa-4tLyQ0GihXhCJimU0C/update-zulip-icon.jpg\">update-zulip-icon.jpg</a> <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"22433\">@Vlad Korobov</span> Here goes nothing. Not sure I completely understood what you asked for but  here it is; the Bot icon on the current design screen. I reduced the size to 16px to match other icons.</p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/89/9ymUa-4tLyQ0GihXhCJimU0C/update-zulip-icon.jpg\" title=\"update-zulip-icon.jpg\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/2/89/9ymUa-4tLyQ0GihXhCJimU0C/update-zulip-icon.jpg\"></a></div>",
